Package: confschedlr
Title: Organise submitted papers into time slots to schedule a conference
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Ben", "Marwick", email = "benmarwick@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Given a table authors and the titles of their papers, this package 
    contains functions to group the papers into time slots for a conference with 
    parallel sessions. The functions will check for schedule clashes so that no 
    author will scheduled to present in two concurrent slots.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.0)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
URL: https://github.com/benmarwick/confschedlr
BugReports: https://github.com/benmarwick/confschedlr/issues
Imports: bookdown, tm, topicmodels, readxl, Rmpfr, tidyverse
Suggests: testthat
